### Current State
The ProtectedFilter infrastructure exists and is well-tested in `collect/protected.rs`, but it's NEVER used in any agent command. All agent commands iterate directly over raw scan results.

### Layered Filtering Architecture

After implementing all fixes, filtering works in layers:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    FILTERING LAYERS                          │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Layer 1: quick_scan (tj8m.4)                                │
│   - Filters kernel threads by PPID (0, 2)                   │
│   - Controlled by --include-kernel-threads flag             │
│   - Defense at collection time                              │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Layer 2: ProtectedFilter (THIS TASK)                        │
│   - Filters by policy patterns (systemd, sshd, etc.)        │
│   - Filters by protected users (root)                       │
│   - Filters by never_kill_pid/ppid from policy              │
│   - Defense at inference time                               │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Layer 3: Guardrails in apply (future)                       │
│   - Final safety gates before action execution              │
│   - Rate limits (max_kills_per_run, etc.)                   │
│   - Defense at action time                                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Why multiple layers?**
- Defense in depth: if one layer fails, others catch it
- Different control points: user can enable kernel threads in scan but policy still protects
- Separation of concerns: quick_scan handles kernel threads, ProtectedFilter handles policy

### Commands That Need ProtectedFilter

| Command | Needs Filter? | Reason |
|---------|--------------|--------|
| `agent plan` | **YES** | Generates kill/review recommendations |
| `agent apply` | **YES (CRITICAL)** | Executes actions - must filter before action |
| `agent explain` | Optional | Read-only, but should warn if explaining protected |
| `scan` | No | Raw data output, filtering is at inference |

